  Source:
    Title: Young India
    Editor: M. K. Gandhi
    Locus:
      Date: 25 April 1929
---
That faith is of little value which can flourish only in fair weather,
Faith in order to be of any value has to survive the severest trials,
Your faith is a whited sepulchre if it cannot stand the calumny of the
whole world.
